        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-11-29 19:04:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nYes, rather than spending a long time to run and then exiting the test, it would be better to compute estimated completion time on each loop based on the average rate for all the data written so far. That will avoid overly optimistic estimates for writes to cache at the start if the test.\n\nIt might be useful to make this a function in test framework, since we do similar checks in many other tests (e.g. oos.sh and such). \n\nPossibly even a better solution would be to examine the tests that are writing a lot of data and see if they can be combined?  Maybe we don't need oos.sh at all if oos2.sh runs?  Maybe we don't need either if this test can check all of those things and only run once?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
